title: A Victorian Household
description: A look at the lives of a middle class family of Victorian England, as seen through the diaries kept by Marion Sanbourne from 1881 to 1914. Married to Punch cartoonist Linley Sanbourne, she was acquainted with a number of artists of the time, including Du Maurier, Tenniel, Watts, Crane, and Oscar Wilde. Distributed by Books International. Annotation c. by Book News, Inc., Portland, Or.
author: Shirley Nicholson
